# Line-ending policy — critical for a cross-platform, GitHub-hosted plugin.
#
# The launcher `bin/runcode` is an extensionless, shebang'd POSIX sh script that
# macOS/Linux run DIRECTLY (`#!/bin/sh`). If git ever checks it out with CRLF (a
# Windows clone with core.autocrlf=true would do exactly that), the shebang
# becomes `/bin/sh\r` and POSIX fails it with "bad interpreter: No such file or
# directory". So pin every text file to LF…
* text=auto eol=lf

# …force the POSIX launcher + its tests to LF no matter the client's autocrlf…
bin/runcode          text eol=lf
tests/test_launcher.sh text eol=lf

# …and keep the Windows launchers as CRLF (cmd.exe / PowerShell are happiest
# with CRLF).
bin/runcode.cmd  text eol=crlf
bin/runcode.ps1  text eol=crlf
